						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up infront of the image of Āñjanēya in the tank bed to the north-east of the village.</p>						

						<p>This dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1466;</hi> other details are not known. It is corresponds to 1544 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Highly damaged. It register gift of some taxes as <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi> like <hi rend="italic">kānika</hi> probably to the temple at village Jonnavaram by Māḍrāju Rājayyadēva mahārāju.</p>						

						</summary>
